Vue CLI projects already use `mini-css-extract-plugin`, so inserting a new one in `configureWebpack` would result in duplicate CSS processing, as you discovered.

Instead, you could configure the existing plugin through [`css.extract`](https://cli.vuejs.org/config/#css-extract) in `vue.config.js`. It should look similar to this:

```js
// vue.config.js
module.exports = {
  //...
  configureWebpack: {
    output: {
      filename: &quot;./js/sales-report.js&quot;
    }
  },
  chainWebpack: config =&gt; {
    config.optimization.delete(&quot;splitChunks&quot;);
  },
  css: {
    extract: {
      filename: &quot;/css/sales-report.css&quot;
    }
  }
}
```

